<h1>Info for Section 0</h1>

<b>HTML</b>
<p>HyperText Markup Language is the the thing that glues everything together.
Hyper links glues the pages together. Browsers makes request to internet to servers</p>

<b>HTML is made up of:</b>
<p>Text content what you see
 markup what it looks like
 references to other doc
 links to other pages
</p>
<b>HTML markup</b>
<p>< name>contents< /name>
  opening tag    closing tag
  All of it is Element
  b is bold
  em is italics
</p>
<b>HTML Attributes</b>
<p>< tag ATTR="value"> contents < /tag>
Anchor - < a> - for making links
< a href="www.reddit.com">derp< /a>
</p>
<b>Images</b>
<p><img> - images
<img src="url" alt="text">
src is the url of image
alt is required, for broken request and for blind people
It is a void tag as it has no content so needs no closing tag
</p>

<b>WHITESPACE</b>
<p>all space turns into single space
<br> break (void tag) put this to enter line
< p> paragraph
< p>content< /p>
</p>
<b>inline/block</b>
<p>< br> - inline < p> - block

br ends the line
p tag makes an invisible box
</p>
<b>span / div</b>
<p>< span>text< /span>
span is inline
< div>text< /div>
div is block
</p>
HTML DOCUMENTS
<p>< !DOCTYPE HTML> - doctype<br>
< html><br>
< head><br>
  < title>Title!< /title><br>
< /head><br>
< body><br>
< b>content< /b> stuff you see of the screen
< /body><br>
< /html>
</p>
